### System:
You are an AI assistant that follows instruction extremely well. Help as much as you can.

### User:
Before Cam broke his right arm, he was able to type 9 words per minute on his phone.  After he broke his arm, he had to use his left hand for a while, and he could only type 6 words per minute. What is the difference between the number of words he could type in 5 minutes before and after he broke his arm

### Response:


The difference between the number of words Cam could type in 5 minutes before he broke his arm and after he broke his arm is:

6 - 9 = -3

This means that in 5 minutes before he broke his arm, Cam was able to type 9 words per minute, but after he broke his arm, he could only type 6 words per minute. Therefore, he was able to type a total of 6 x 5 = 30 words in 5 minutes before he broke his arm, and 6 x 5 = 30 words in 5 minutes after he broke his arm. The difference is -3, which means he was able to type 30 - 9 = 21 words less in 5 minutes after he broke his arm than before he broke his arm.
